7
00:00:39,170 --> 00:00:44,253
[SPEAKER_04]: The purpose of this meeting is to discuss the proposed food truck ordinance, paper 20-020.

8
00:00:44,733 --> 00:00:51,957
[SPEAKER_04]: The committee has invited Interim Economic Development Director, Victor Schrader and a representative of the Office of Planning, Development and Sustainability to attend this meeting.

9
00:00:52,856 --> 00:00:57,457
[SPEAKER_04]: For further information, aids and accommodations, contact the city clerk at 781-393-2425.

10
00:00:57,517 --> 00:01:00,198
[SPEAKER_04]: Sincerely yours, Nicole Morrell, Council President.

11
00:01:00,998 --> 00:01:05,219
[SPEAKER_04]: So we had met on this paper a few months back, and I think it was a few months at this point.

12
00:01:05,559 --> 00:01:18,522
[SPEAKER_04]: We had a number of resolutions and questions, and then asked Economic Development Director Schrader if they could come back with some proposed language for an updated version of this ordinance, unless

13
00:01:19,018 --> 00:01:21,119
[SPEAKER_04]: Councilors have any questions to start?

14
00:01:21,179 --> 00:01:27,080
[SPEAKER_04]: I can hand it off to Victor to give us an update of responses to those past questions and motions.

15
00:01:29,041 --> 00:01:37,083
[SPEAKER_04]: Seeing none, Victor, if you wanna share with us the changes that you've proposed in response to the discussion we last had.

16
00:01:39,026 --> 00:01:41,587
[SPEAKER_02]: Yeah, thank you, President morale.

17
00:01:42,027 --> 00:01:44,788
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you, counselor sorry I'm not able to be there in person tonight.

18
00:01:46,389 --> 00:01:52,411
[SPEAKER_02]: As the President mentioned the last time we met we reviewed a draft ordinance that was proposed in 2016.

19
00:01:55,612 --> 00:02:01,715
[SPEAKER_02]: And we use this as a starting point to incorporate the feedback that we received from council.

20
00:02:02,635 --> 00:02:10,759
[SPEAKER_02]: The Chamber of Commerce was also in attendance and a couple of members of the public.

21
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:19,722
[SPEAKER_02]: So we did our best to incorporate that feedback and have a draft for you to review tonight.

22
00:02:20,923 --> 00:02:22,944
