00:02:44,339 --> 00:02:45,200
[SPEAKER_02]: Just in summary,

30
00:02:47,235 --> 00:03:03,518
[SPEAKER_02]: The review that we've done as staff since we last met is to incorporate some of the experience we've gathered processing applications over the last couple of years.

31
00:03:03,818 --> 00:03:12,640
[SPEAKER_02]: Those proposals have been running through our office, and then we've been presenting them to you all for consideration.

32
00:03:18,235 --> 00:03:27,618
[SPEAKER_02]: incorporated some input from the health director, who raised some concerns that I think we'd like to address tonight.

33
00:03:28,758 --> 00:03:37,261
[SPEAKER_02]: And we have shared the draft with the Chamber of Commerce as well, and they've provided some feedback that is helpful and relevant.

34
00:03:38,741 --> 00:03:44,062
[SPEAKER_04]: In general, the approach- On the 20th, I missed that, I apologize.

35
00:03:44,102 --> 00:03:46,083
[SPEAKER_04]: So I didn't get that after the council, that's on me.

36
00:03:46,790 --> 00:03:47,771
[SPEAKER_04]: I just sent it to the clerk.

37
00:03:48,251 --> 00:03:48,851
[SPEAKER_04]: I apologize.

38
00:03:48,891 --> 00:03:49,972
[SPEAKER_04]: I missed that in my inbox.

39
00:03:51,073 --> 00:03:51,173
[SPEAKER_02]: OK.

40
00:03:51,713 --> 00:03:55,816
[SPEAKER_02]: I'll pull up a draft, a copy of it, so we can walk through it together if you'd like.

41
00:03:57,718 --> 00:04:13,789
[SPEAKER_02]: Just in general, the approach we've taken with this draft is to establish an administrative approval process for one-day mobile food vendor licenses and special event mobile food vendor licenses.

42
00:04:13,849 --> 00:04:14,990
[SPEAKER_02]: So those are two types.

43
00:04:17,411 --> 00:04:40,526
[SPEAKER_02]: And that's really based on what we heard from council and really the chamber to limit the license types to temporary, but also be able to accommodate special events and provide the option for mobile food vendors to operate in the city on a limited basis.

44
00:04:42,500 --> 00:05:00,585
[SPEAKER_02]: The ordinance, as it's written, this draft does not allow for ongoing long-term food truck licenses, mobile food vendor licenses, and does not allow mobile food vendors to drive through the community.

45
00:05:00,645 --> 00:05:03,086
[SPEAKER_02]: They have to be stationary in a specific location.

46
00:05:05,646 --> 00:05:07,547
[SPEAKER_02]: And the approval process will be

47
00:05:09,273 --> 00:05:15,417
[SPEAKER_02]: The license application will be reviewed and approved by the Department of Health on behalf of the Board of Health.

48
00:05:17,299 --> 00:05:22,803
[SPEAKER_02]: And this part of the ordinance, I believe, needs some further legal review.

49
00:05:22,823 --> 00:05:33,992
[SPEAKER_02]: And I'll point out some areas, some language that we think is important to review with legal counsel so that it's clean and clear.

50
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:37,981
[SPEAKER_02]: Any questions so far?

51
00:05:38,501 --> 00:05:38,801
[SPEAKER_02]: Thoughts?

52
00:05:40,162 --> 00:05:40,902
[SPEAKER_02]: I can continue.

53
