[SPEAKER_09]: Going through the process right now,

58
00:05:58,088 --> 00:06:04,271
[SPEAKER_09]: with special permits by this council, I think it's okay until we have legal representation.

59
00:06:04,931 --> 00:06:07,392
[SPEAKER_09]: Because again, this has to go back to KP law.

60
00:06:08,172 --> 00:06:09,973
[SPEAKER_09]: And KP law is going to be spending more money.

61
00:06:10,393 --> 00:06:13,375
[SPEAKER_09]: We still haven't gotten an update of what what's being paid out.

62
00:06:13,835 --> 00:06:15,676
[SPEAKER_09]: We still don't know what our budget looks like.

63
00:06:16,436 --> 00:06:18,557
[SPEAKER_09]: And we have a bunch of money papers coming on after this.

64
00:06:19,017 --> 00:06:20,658
[SPEAKER_09]: I just think we need to slow down

65
00:06:21,857 --> 00:06:32,001
[SPEAKER_09]: And the ordinances that we have in place right now, I think we need to put a hard stop on this, Madam President, for the fact that we keep sending things out to KP Law.

66
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:39,124
[SPEAKER_09]: This is something that a city solicitor does as part of their salary.

67
00:06:39,164 --> 00:06:43,746
[SPEAKER_09]: This is something that started in 2016, seven years ago.

68
00:06:43,766 --> 00:06:48,808
[SPEAKER_09]: Now here we are, we're still sending paperwork, we're still sending work to KP Law.

69
00:06:51,308 --> 00:06:55,891
[SPEAKER_09]: We don't know if we're getting murdered in our finances, we don't know.

70
00:06:55,911 --> 00:07:06,057
[SPEAKER_09]: So I really, my recommendation, I'm gonna have a motion that we table everything until we have a city solicitor and continue with what we have.

71
00:07:06,697 --> 00:07:18,765
[SPEAKER_09]: I appreciate Victor doing the work and coming back, but when I hear the first comment that this has to be reviewed by legal counsel again, guys, this is, when it's enough enough, when are we gonna stop?

72
00:07:19,695 --> 00:07:21,296
[SPEAKER_09]: We're bleeding and we don't know how bad.

73
00:07:22,476 --> 00:07:36,241
[SPEAKER_09]: So again, please, this is getting to be redundant now with my dialogue, but I'm at the point where I'm begging for my fellow colleagues to understand that we need to stop.

74
00:07:36,261 --> 00:07:40,423
[SPEAKER_09]: There's gotta be a point that we stop until we get what we need.

75
00:07:40,463 --> 00:07:43,744
[SPEAKER_09]: We're making decisions financially

76
00:07:46,540 --> 00:07:51,164
[SPEAKER_09]: We're knowing nothing, not understanding anything, not having any paperwork in front of us.

77
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:55,287
[SPEAKER_09]: And these low-hanging fruit situations, we can wait.

78
00:07:57,329 --> 00:07:58,029
[SPEAKER_09]: We've been doing it.

79
00:07:58,390 --> 00:07:59,451
[SPEAKER_09]: It hasn't hurt anybody.

80
00:07:59,791 --> 00:08:06,797
[SPEAKER_09]: We know that, but the brick-and-mortar businesses don't want food trucks near their establishments, and nor should they be.

81
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:11,041
[SPEAKER_09]: But here we are, again, gonna be reaching out.

82
00:08:11,121 --> 00:08:22,946
[SPEAKER_09]: And what I've been told, every time they pick up the phone, KP law, because you know, $700, because I guarantee you, this doesn't fall in the $6,800 plan that we made a few years back.

83
00:08:25,608 --> 00:08:28,429
[SPEAKER_09]: This wasn't, the ordinances went through our city solicitor.

84
00:08:29,656 --> 00:08:35,437
[SPEAKER_09]: So again, I apologize for my negativity, but I can only hold in so much.

85
00:08:35,477 --> 00:08:39,858
[SPEAKER_09]: I'm at the point right now that the frustration is unbearable.

86
00:08:40,199 --> 00:08:42,199
[SPEAKER_09]: So Victor, again, I apologize.

87
00:08:42,299 --> 00:08:43,319
[SPEAKER_09]: You do amazing work.

88
00:08:43,399 --> 00:08:47,640
[SPEAKER_09]: We appreciate everything you do, but I hope you understand my frustration.

89
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:50,501
[SPEAKER_09]: This is something we can hold on.

90
00:08:50,861 --> 00:08:53,922
