109
00:10:21,688 --> 00:10:22,368
[SPEAKER_04]: Victor, if you want to go ahead.

110
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:23,710
[SPEAKER_02]: Okay, thank you.

111
00:10:25,871 --> 00:10:35,715
[SPEAKER_02]: Some substantive changes that we've made to the draft since the last committee of the whole are to simplify the definitions.

112
00:10:35,775 --> 00:10:40,397
[SPEAKER_02]: There were a number of overlapping definitions, and this was mostly just language cleanup.

113
00:10:41,918 --> 00:10:44,519
[SPEAKER_02]: We changed permit to license in all instances.

114
00:10:46,099 --> 00:10:47,320
[SPEAKER_02]: We changed the

115
00:10:48,622 --> 00:10:57,706
[SPEAKER_02]: There were references to the Director of Public Health, and we changed that to the Board of Health, per the recommendation of our current Director of Public Health.

116
00:10:59,127 --> 00:11:04,930
[SPEAKER_02]: We updated some of the application requirements based on health department input.

117
00:11:07,351 --> 00:11:09,752
[SPEAKER_02]: We added a special permit provision.

118
00:11:12,931 --> 00:11:20,036
[SPEAKER_02]: This would allow unusual circumstances to come before city council for review.

119
00:11:20,056 --> 00:11:21,277
[SPEAKER_02]: That's the idea here.

120
00:11:23,999 --> 00:11:40,931
[SPEAKER_02]: There are unforeseeable situations that may not be covered under the ordinance, so we thought it was appropriate for there to be a process for those applications to be heard and reviewed and a determination made.

121
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:49,073
[SPEAKER_02]: And then we added a penalty for one year suspension if trucks are operating without a license.

122
00:11:49,153 --> 00:11:54,458
[SPEAKER_02]: So we thought that was an appropriate clause to include as well.

123
00:11:57,427 --> 00:12:10,395
[SPEAKER_02]: And then there's a clause in there allowing the Board of Health to promulgate additional rules and regulations, which is pretty typical in these ordinances.

124
00:12:10,455 --> 00:12:20,562
[SPEAKER_02]: If you remember from the outdoor dining ordinance, we actually separated some of the rules and regulations from the ordinance and gave authority to the

125
00:12:27,235 --> 00:12:31,697
[SPEAKER_02]: building department to establish on an annual basis.

126
00:12:36,058 --> 00:12:39,880
[SPEAKER_02]: Would it be helpful at this point if I brought up the ordinance so we could all look at it together?

127
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:43,161
[SPEAKER_02]: What's the best way to do this, Chair?

128
00:12:44,181 --> 00:12:44,842
[SPEAKER_04]: Yes, that would be great.

129
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:45,342
[SPEAKER_02]: OK.

130
00:12:56,252 --> 00:12:57,053
[SPEAKER_05]: One moment.

131
00:13:13,885 --> 00:13:15,185
[SPEAKER_02]: This is a clean copy.

132
00:13:16,246 --> 00:13:18,928
[SPEAKER_02]: Maybe I'll pull up the redlined version.

133
00:13:20,149 --> 00:13:21,590
[SPEAKER_04]: Yeah, if you could, that would be appreciated.

134
00:13:41,287 --> 00:13:49,094
[SPEAKER_02]: Okay, so if you were to do a side-by-side of the 2016 draft in this draft, it would look very similar.

135
00:13:50,755 --> 00:13:52,657
[SPEAKER_02]: As you'll see, some small language changes.

136
00:13:53,718 --> 00:14:02,246
[SPEAKER_02]: We really wanted to make it clear that this ordinance is for allowing for one day and special events only.

137
00:14:06,985 --> 00:14:18,352
[SPEAKER_02]: There's some language here with the definition of mobile food vendor that probably needs some adjustment to account for carts and other types of apparatus.

138
00:14:26,617 --> 00:14:32,200
[SPEAKER_02]: Under the special events mobile food vendor license section, we added some language

139
00:14:33,187 --> 00:14:42,511
[SPEAKER_02]: to make it clear that the duration of the license may be for more than one day, but no longer than the event itself.

140
00:14:43,432 --> 00:14:45,153
[SPEAKER_02]: So there's clarity there.

141
00:14:54,777 --> 00:14:58,659
[SPEAKER_02]: License fees would be established by the Board of Health.

142
00:15:01,088 --> 00:15:07,449
[SPEAKER_02]: The application requirements section is largely the same, some minor language changes.

143
00:15:07,469 --> 00:15:16,631
[SPEAKER_02]: This section was added by the Department of Health requesting some additional information from applicants.

144
00:15:22,733 --> 00:15:23,813
[SPEAKER_02]: I think we want to

145
00:15:25,198 --> 00:15:32,786
[SPEAKER_02]: get some input on whether this is the general liability policy requirement and whether $1 million per claim is appropriate.

146
00:15:38,372 --> 00:15:45,280
[SPEAKER_02]: In some cases, a mobile food vendor will require a state hawker's license, so we included a section referencing that.

147
00:15:54,906 --> 00:16:07,051
[SPEAKER_02]: And then this section is a carryover from the 2016 draft, asking for advisory reports from a number of departments, city departments.

148
00:16:10,692 --> 00:16:13,093
[SPEAKER_02]: We know that our departments have a lot on their plates.

149
00:16:13,414 --> 00:16:18,055
[SPEAKER_02]: And in some cases, this is appropriate and others maybe not, not necessary.

150
00:16:20,424 --> 00:16:23,186
[SPEAKER_02]: We'd ask for some additional time to go back to these departments.

151
00:16:23,206 --> 00:16:25,188
[SPEAKER_02]: We haven't really had a conversation with them.

152
00:16:25,768 --> 00:16:29,472
[SPEAKER_02]: I wanted to get input from the council as to whether you thought this was important or not.

153
00:16:30,132 --> 00:16:36,397
[SPEAKER_02]: And then we can go back and have a conversation with them about this.

154
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:43,003
[SPEAKER_02]: And similarly, the background check requirement.

155
00:16:47,019 --> 00:17:05,404
[SPEAKER_02]: I think this is something that legal will have to weigh in on at some point, because I know there's complexities to background checks, and I don't know that this language is necessary or is constructed properly.

156
00:17:09,586 --> 00:17:10,566
[SPEAKER_02]: Any feedback so far?

157
